What are the main affected groups?
Syphilis and gonorrhea are found mostly in men who have sex with men.
The Robert Koch Institute assumes that in at least four out of every five cases of syphilis reported in Germany, the transfer occurs as a result of sexual intercourse between men.
Heterosexual adults with frequently occurring sexually transmitted diseases are chlamydia infections, trichomoniasis, candidiasis (fung) feud, gonorrhea and human papillomavirus.
The prevalence of HIV among heterosexual adults is relatively low - but about 20 percent of new HIV infections occur in this group.
Among young people, chlamydia infections are more common than among other population groups.
