Manning's lawyer filed an official objection to Manning's mistreatment in January 2011.
In April 2011, Manning was transferred to a military prison in Fort Livenworth, Kansas.
In addition, on Friday, the judge asked Manning about the statement he made during his testimony on Thursday that after being forced to sleep naked in his cell in Kwantiko, he was forced to stand naked in front of guards and other prisoners in the morning.
